<br>
         His horses nostrils shooting jets of white streams into the air, on it's sides a quiver of spears holding at least ten deadly spears. He himself was covered in a strange collection of armor. His pants covered in a thick rawhide. His boots made over the same material but the shins covered with a thick metal sheet. His chest covered a strange armor of chains strapped together over his chest. The shiny metal was coated with black ash.<br>
<br>
          He was the only male on this side most likely, but against gods it mattered little. His wrist were covered with two different looking gauntlets one gold and the other silver. He had his mystical blade over his back the runes seemingly glowing with power. His was ready for this the tension in the air was electric and the immortal was ready to try his hand.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualastorofancients.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alastor of Ancients</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/14/01 5:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://caspervandien.net/sleepyhollow/themovie/photos/images/indeximageov.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Heh</span><hr size=1> (( that was me just forgot to switch a post thingy.. )) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 394<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/14/01 5:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ..The Norseman..</span><hr size=1>  Dawn shifted some atop the saddle of her horse, feet fitting loosely and edgy into the stirrups. Although she looked nervous, and paranoid, inside she was focused. For yards, maybe miles, her ears could hear the shuffling of prepared feet, and the snorts of a rather angry horse. <br>
<br>
 Underneath the war mask, lips formed into a cynical grin. Even a hint of those defining emerald eyes showed underneath the layer of crimson that coated her eyes. It was hatred and blood lust, blood shed and killing, that covered the truth in her soul. <br>
<br>
 Hearing the snorts once more, Dawn glanced over her right shoulder, a brow raised at the presence of Alastor on their side. Logic tugged into her mind, everyone would think he was there to betray him, but the aura he gave off told otherwise. <br>
<br>
 A simple nod was given to the norseman, and his horse, before Dawn turned her head back to face forward. To face the gods. [I'm not honoring any NPC's.] There was.. let's see.. Hecate, Eris, Poseidon, Hypnos, and Fogstone. The assassin couldn't help but snicker, glancing to around at the amazons.<br>
<br>
 Yup, they were all the ego manics each one of them had proven to upset, because they couldn't get their way, outside of their cushy life, and spoiled world. But then, they had been the stupid ones to try and intimidate the amazons. <p>
