<br>
  &quot;Lo, there do I see my father <br>
   Lo, there do I see my mother and my sisters&quot;<br>
<br>
         As he trotted he thought of past and present blended into one as he moved.  He moved along as his head turned slowly to look at the grizzly nest to him, he gave another nod.  He looked back ahead of himself as he leveled his eyes on Hippolyte. <br>
       <br>
&quot;and my brothers<br>
Lo, there do I see the line of my people back<br>
to the beginning&quot;<br>
<br>
         As he moved towards her his hand lingered down next to his saddle pulling a long spear the tip a strange black rock, brimstone. He moved his horse closer to hers as he picked up speed riding past Del.<br>
<br>
&quot;Lo, they do call to me<br>
They bid me take place among them<br>
in the Halls of Valhalla<br>
Where the brave may live forever...&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp He matched her speed slowly up next to her as he looks over at Hippolyte spear in hand. His lips curl slightly as he nods over to her. His hair long once more like before to his mid-back his chin shaved clean. The demon of the battlefeild had returned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Today is a good day for War.&quot;<br>
