His face dark with the passion of war. In his right hand he held the sword of war which he swung with great ease. Walking to the centre he took the sword and smashed it deep into the ground, where there was a massive rumbling before he withdrew it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't tell me you decided to fight a war without the God of War, although I must admit I'm in a bit of a dither to which side I should be on. After all I am some of the Amazon's fathers, and my favourite assasin is there as well. But then they wouldn't want to me to fight with them beause they want to stand up for themselves and I don't blame them. Then of course there are my fellow gods, who have manipulated, tricked and decieved people for years...I'm really at a loss here!&quot;<br>
*He sits down on the battlefield*<br>
<br>
&quot;What a dilemna&quot;<br>
&quot;I'm not going to flip a coin...but I've decided which side I'm on...and I don't care if they don't want me to help...I for once don't care about worship etc...but when I have the chance to get back at some of my 'godly friends' plus also I don't think you should make people worship gods that they don't want to believe in or change their worship...its sounds a very strange thing for me to say...but hey! Its me...give me credit&quot;<br>
<br>
